verbs.description: overempty (third-person singular simple present overempties, present participle overemptying, simple past and past participle overemptied)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make too empty; to exhaust.
examples: […]  would be very loth to come behind the fashion, in new fangledness of the manner, if not in costliness of the matter, which perhaps might overempty their husbands  purses
